id: pm-bd3u
title: "SDK invoke helpers for search providers, vector store adapters and migrations"
description: "Complete the extension-invoke testing surface so every executable registration surface has a runRegistered*ForTest helper to match its assertRegistered* counterpart. Adds runRegisteredSearchProviderForTest (query/embed/embedBatch/queryExpansion/rerank), runRegisteredVectorStoreAdapterForTest (query/upsert/delete), and runRegisteredMigrationForTest (run). Each resolves the registered definition via the same runtime resolver the host uses (resolveRegisteredSearchProvider, resolveRegisteredVectorStoreAdapter, getMigrationRuntimeDefinition), invokes runtime_definition over definition, and throws a descriptive error when the registration or operation is absent. Closes the gap left by pm-miqm/pm-owm0 which covered commands, hooks and the five overrides but not these three operation surfaces."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk",pm-cli,sdk-testing
created_at: "2026-06-21T17:54:13.581Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-21T17:54:34.122Z"
assignee: claude-code-agent
author: claude-code-agent
value: "Package authors can unit-test the runtime behavior of custom search providers, vector store adapters and migrations through stable SDK entry points, not private registry internals"
parent: pm-ugqx
